Interface Traversal<S,T,A,B>

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ListTraversal

    public interface Traversal<S,T,A,B>
extends Wander<S::A,T::B>, Traversal<S::A,T::B>, Optic<TraversalP _,S::A,T::B>
    A traversal is an optic that implements a structure-preserving transformation for (i.e. traverses over) some field of an object. It provides functionality to traverse over some fields of a structure and to transform those fields in the context of an effect.

    The operation performed by traversals is analogous to Traversable, which defines a structure-preserving transformation in the context of an effectful transformation.

    See Also:
    Traversable
